main event: Two silver objects were observed in the sky for fifteen minutes.
interesting points: The objects appeared to be moving at five times the speed of the wind, which does not clearly support the balloon theory.
Two qualified balloon directors stated that the objects were part of Navy Project Moby Dick, suggesting they were balloons.
The description of the sighting led to the conclusion that the objects were probably balloons.
There were no photographs included in the report.
The report was submitted by a civilian source.
